Mysterious WWI soldier known as the 'Handsome Man' was used to front Woolworths' 'Fresh in our memories' ad campaign . 
  Little is known about the soldier but he was a soldier of the First Australian Imperial Force . 
  The image was featured in a 2008 Australian War Memorial exhibition . 
  Woolworth's has been slammed for commercialising the centenary of Anzac . 
  Minister for Veterans' Affairs Michael Ronaldson forced the company to take down the website . 
  The supermarket giant also failed to seek permission for the word 'Anzac' The company launched the campaign and website on Anzac Day . 
 